    dc:description "Fig. 45. Distribution of Begonia sect. Ephemera Moonlight in Peru and surrounding countries. A. B. fischeri Schrank (red). B. B. hirtella Link (red). Black lines indicate country borders, grey lines indicate major administrative divisions, blue lines indicate rivers, and shading indicates elevation." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8178397/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8178401>
    dc:description "Fig. 47. Begonia hirtella Link. A. Habit. B. Stipule. C. Leaf, adaxial surface. D. Leaf, abaxial surface. E. Inflorescence. F. Staminate flower, side view. G. Staminate flower, front view. H. Tepal of staminate flower. I. Androecium, side view. J. Pistillate flower, side view. K. Pistillate flower, front view. L. Cross section of ovary. M. Developing fruit, side view. N. Pistils, side view. O. Smallest tepal of pistillate flower. P. Largest tepal of pistillate flower. Q. Bracteole. All photographs taken by D.A. Purvis from a glasshouse weed in the living collections of the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8178401/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

